{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778976908462,"sessionID":"ses_1ccba5ea0ffeccv3jvRnsohjU4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_DKJN69KhOAzA2b1GR3r1wwQt","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+The two disjointness axioms involving `UBERON:0000001` and GO cellular terms have been moved out of the OBO edit file and into the imported `disjoint_union_over.owl` component, avoiding label-less GO term frames on OBO serialization.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+## Summary\n+\n+This addresses issue #3651 by moving the problematic GO disjointness axioms out of `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` and into `src/ontology/components/disjoint_union_over.owl`, which is already imported by the edit file.\n+\n+## Rationale\n+\n+The axioms are semantically unchanged as OWL `DisjointClasses` axioms, but no longer require label-less GO term frames in the OBO edit file. This avoids the OBO serialization issue described in the issue, where OWLAPI-based serialization can attach symmetric disjointness tags to GO frames and create missing-label errors.\n+\n+## Changes\n+\n+- Removed the two label-less GO term frames from `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`:\n+- `GO:0005623 disjoint_from UBERON:0000001`\n+- `GO:0110165 disjoint_from UBERON:0000001`\n+- Added equivalent OWL Functional Syntax axioms to `src/ontology/components/disjoint_union_over.owl`:\n+- `DisjointClasses(GO_0005623 UBERON_0000001)`\n+- `DisjointClasses(GO_0110165 UBERON_0000001)`\n+\n+## Checklist\n+\n+- Read imported issue context and maintainer comment recommending a component-based solution.\n+- Checked existing `UBERON:0000001`, `GO:0005623`, and `GO:0110165` serialization in `uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- Confirmed `disjoint_union_over.owl` is already imported by `uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- Preserved OWL semantics by moving, not deleting, the disjointness axioms.\n+- Re-serialized `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` with ROBOT.\n+- Validated OBO syntax with `robot convert -i src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo -f obo`.\n+- Validated component OWL syntax with `robot convert -i src/ontology/components/disjoint_union_over.owl -f ofn`.\n+- Confirmed the GO frames are no longer present in `uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- Confirmed the two equivalent `DisjointClasses` axioms are present in the component.\n+\n+## Identifier Notes\n+\n+OLS lookups confirmed that `UBERON:0000001` and `GO:0110165` are current, and that `GO:0005623` exists but is obsolete in GO. This PR does not introduce a new biological assertion for `GO:0005623`; it preserves the pre-existing disjointness axiom in a serialization-safe component.\n+\n+@dragon-ai-agent\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,3 @@\n+Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+The two disjointness axioms involving `UBERON:0000001` and GO cellular terms have been moved out of the OBO edit file and into the imported `disjoint_union_over.owl` component, avoiding label-less GO term frames on OBO serialization.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+## Summary\n+\n+This addresses issue #3651 by moving the problematic GO disjointness axioms out of `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` and into `src/ontology/components/disjoint_union_over.owl`, which is already imported by the edit file.\n+\n+## Rationale\n+\n+The axioms are semantically unchanged as OWL `DisjointClasses` axioms, but no longer require label-less GO term frames in the OBO edit file. This avoids the OBO serialization issue described in the issue, where OWLAPI-based serialization can attach symmetric disjointness tags to GO frames and create missing-label errors.\n+\n+## Changes\n+\n+- Removed the two label-less GO term frames from `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`:\n+- `GO:0005623 disjoint_from UBERON:0000001`\n+- `GO:0110165 disjoint_from UBERON:0000001`\n+- Added equivalent OWL Functional Syntax axioms to `src/ontology/components/disjoint_union_over.owl`:\n+- `DisjointClasses(GO_0005623 UBERON_0000001)`\n+- `DisjointClasses(GO_0110165 UBERON_0000001)`\n+\n+## Checklist\n+\n+- Read imported issue context and maintainer comment recommending a component-based solution.\n+- Checked existing `UBERON:0000001`, `GO:0005623`, and `GO:0110165` serialization in `uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- Confirmed `disjoint_union_over.owl` is already imported by `uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- Preserved OWL semantics by moving, not deleting, the disjointness axioms.\n+- Re-serialized `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` with ROBOT.\n+- Validated OBO syntax with `robot convert -i src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo -f obo`.\n+- Validated component OWL syntax with `robot convert -i src/ontology/components/disjoint_union_over.owl -f ofn`.\n+- Confirmed the GO frames are no longer present in `uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- Confirmed the two equivalent `DisjointClasses` axioms are present in the component.\n+\n+## Identifier Notes\n+\n+OLS lookups confirmed that `UBERON:0000001` and `GO:0110165` are current, and that `GO:0005623` exists but is obsolete in GO. This PR does not introduce a new biological assertion for `GO:0005623`; it preserves the pre-existing disjointness axiom in a serialization-safe component.\n+\n+@dragon-ai-agent\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.